<subSubSection id="E7B8656FC6231356FF0DFBF5FBDFFC95" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AF1D36E4C6231357FF0DFBF5FDD9FA03" blockId="2.[151,1437,1114,2036]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FF0DFBF5FE93FBB3" bold="true" box="[151,282,1114,1140]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Peritrematal shields truncate behind fourth pair of coxae, and separated by triangular slit from body margin behind posterior peritrematal setae. Two pairs of peritrematal setae present, anterior peritrematal setae short, smooth or very finely pilose, posterior peritrematal setae considerably longer (
<number id="196A24C3C6231357FB27FB0AFB71FB78" box="[1213,1272,1189,1215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="6.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.0">3–10</number>
times as long as anterior setae), finely pilose or smooth, apically tapering. Both pairs inserted dorsally on peritrematal shield. Peritremes short, reaching only posterior edge of third pair of coxae. Adgenital gland openings present, situated on conspicuous platelets. One pair of post-genital sclerites often present. Ventri-anal shield caudally fused to opisthonotal shield. Anterior margin of ventri-anal shield with two pairs of setae. Ventri-anal pores situated posterolaterally to adanal setae. Epistome with two pairs of longer central points and several shorter spines. Anterior margin of podonotum sloping gradually, setae j 
<number id="196A24C3C6231357FC19FA2AFC06FA58" box="[899,911,1413,1439]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="1.0">1</number>
inserted dorsally. Setae z 
<number id="196A24C3C6231357FB21FA2AFB4EFA58" box="[1211,1223,1413,1439]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="1.0">1</number>
absent. Margin of opisthonotum with 
<number id="196A24C3C6231357FEE1FA05FE2EFA03" box="[379,423,1450,1476]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
pairs of setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF1D36E4C6231357FF5CFA60FA81F843" blockId="2.[151,1437,1114,2036]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FF5CFA60FE3EFA2E" bold="true" box="[198,439,1487,1513]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Notes on the genus.</emphasis>
On the basis of a detailed observation of 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FC04FA7FFB02FA2E" box="[926,1163,1488,1513]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leitnerae">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FC04FA7FFB02FA2E" box="[926,1163,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zerconella leitnerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens collected in 
<collectingCountry id="D7B57674C6231357FF0DFA5AFF77F9C8" box="[151,254,1525,1551]" name="Slovenia" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Slovenia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="D7B57674C6231357FEADFA5AFE04F9C8" box="[311,397,1525,1551]" name="Croatia" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CB334B15C6231357FE04FA5AFDBEF9C8" author="Ujvari" box="[414,567,1525,1551]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" refString="Ujvari, Zs. (2009) Contribution to the Mesostigmata fauna of Slovenia (Acari: Mesostigmata: Zerconidae et Macrochelidae). Acta Entomologica Slovenica, 17, 115 - 124." type="journal article" year="2009">
Ujvári, 
<number id="196A24C3C6231357FE63FA5AFDBEF9C8" box="[505,567,1525,1551]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="2009.201">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CB334B15C6231357FDDEFA5AFD0AF9C8" author="Ujvari" box="[580,643,1525,1551]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" refString="Ujvari, Zs. (2010) Zerconid mites (Acari: Mesostigamata: Zerconidae) from Croatia with description of four new species. Journal of Natural History (in press)." type="book" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
), I raise the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FC13FA5AFAB3F9C8" authority="Willmann, 1953" authorityName="Willmann" authorityYear="1953" box="[905,1338,1525,1551]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Zerconella">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FC13FA5AFC52F9C9" box="[905,987,1525,1550]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zercon</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FC76FA5AFBE3F9C9" box="[1004,1130,1525,1550]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zerconella</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="CB334B15C6231357FBE6FA5AFAB3F9C8" author="Willmann" box="[1148,1338,1525,1551]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" refString="Willmann, C. (1953) Neue Milben aus den ostlichen Alpen. Sitzungsberichte der Osterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Mathematisch - naturwissenschaftliche Klasse, 162, 449 - 519." type="journal article" year="1953">
Willmann, 
<number id="196A24C3C6231357FB65FA5AFAB3F9C8" box="[1279,1338,1525,1551]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="1953.0">1953</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="37992A61C6231357FAD0FA5AFF2FF9F3" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1779,1803]" captionTargetBox="[156,1434,913,1752]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,906,1753]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Ventral idiosoma. 1. Zerconella; 2. Zercon." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196961/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">
Figs 
<number id="196A24C3C6231357FA1CFA5AFF2FF9F3" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="1.2">1, 2</number>
</figureCitation>
) to full generic rank because of the following features: posterior peritrematal setae are very long, smooth or very finely pilose, apically tapering and inserted dorsally in 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FCC1F9EFFC50F99E" box="[859,985,1600,1625]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FCC1F9EFFC50F99E" box="[859,985,1600,1625]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zerconella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; but shorter, usually apically pilose or feathered, often with hyaline ending and inserted ventrally in 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FCE9F9CAFC4CF9B9" authority="C.L.Koch, 1841" authorityName="C.L.Koch" authorityYear="1841" box="[883,965,1637,1662]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FCE9F9CAFC4CF9B9" box="[883,965,1637,1662]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; peritremes are short (neotenic) (
<number id="196A24C3C6231357FACBF9CAFA15F9B8" box="[1361,1436,1637,1663]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="17.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="15.0">15–20</number>
μm), reaching only the posterior edge of the third pair of coxae in 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FC28F924FBB8F963" box="[946,1073,1675,1700]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FC28F924FBB8F963" box="[946,1073,1675,1700]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zerconella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; peritremes are longer (
<number id="196A24C3C6231357FACAF925FA15F963" box="[1360,1436,1674,1700]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="70.0" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="60.0">60–80</number>
μm), reaching the anterior edge of the third pair of coxae in 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FCFBF91FFC3AF90E" authority="C.L.Koch, 1841" authorityName="C.L.Koch" authorityYear="1841" box="[865,947,1712,1737]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FCFBF91FFC3AF90E" box="[865,947,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; post-genital sclerites are usually present in 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FF22F97AFEB5F929" box="[184,316,1749,1774]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FF22F97AFEB5F929" box="[184,316,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zerconella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, absent in 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FE5FF97AFD92F929" authority="C.L.Koch, 1841" authorityName="C.L.Koch" authorityYear="1841" box="[453,539,1749,1774]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FE5FF97AFD92F929" box="[453,539,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the epistome has four long, central points and several shorter spines in 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FF0DF954FE9CF8D3" box="[151,277,1787,1812]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FF0DF954FE9CF8D3" box="[151,277,1787,1812]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zerconella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; usually three long, central points of which the medial one is often apically bifurcate or trifurcate in 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FF2FF88FFE8EF8FE" authority="C.L.Koch, 1841" authorityName="C.L.Koch" authorityYear="1841" box="[181,263,1824,1849]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FF2FF88FFE8EF8FE" box="[181,263,1824,1849]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FE0CF88FFE61F8FE" authority="C.L.Koch, 1841" authorityName="C.L.Koch" authorityYear="1841" box="[406,488,1824,1849]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FE0CF88FFE61F8FE" box="[406,488,1824,1849]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is heterogeneous in important generic characters, such as the number of setae on the anterior margin of the ventri-anal shield and the distribution of dorsal glands, therefore it can not be objectively compared with the genus 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FDD7F8C4FD42F843" box="[589,715,1899,1924]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FDD7F8C4FD42F843" box="[589,715,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zerconella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its current form on the basis of these features.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF1D36E4C6231356FF5FF83FFA01FD7B" blockId="2.[151,1437,1114,2036]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,152,850]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">
Regarding the genus 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FE50F83FFCBBF86D" authority="Blaszak" authorityName="Blaszak" authorityYear="1975" box="[458,818,1936,1962]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Metazercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FE50F83FFDD0F86E" box="[458,601,1936,1961]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Metazercon</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CB334B15C6231357FDF3F83FFCBBF86D" author="Blaszak" box="[617,818,1936,1962]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" refString="Blaszak, C. (1975 a) A revision of the family Zerconidae (Acari, Mesostigmata). Systematic studies on family Zerconidae - I. Acarologia, 17, 553 - 569." type="journal article" year="1975" yearSuffix="a">
Błaszak (
<number id="196A24C3C6231357FD41F83FFC93F86D" box="[731,794,1936,1962]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="1975.0">1975</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
the author described similar generic characters of peritrematal shields, peritrematal setae, peritremes, number of ventri-anal setae, adgenital and post-genital attributes to that of 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FE19F874FDFDF833" box="[387,628,2011,2036]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leitnerae">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FE19F874FDFDF833" box="[387,628,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Zerconella leitnerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However Błaszak omitted to compare 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6231357FBD5F874FB53F833" box="[1103,1242,2011,2036]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Metazercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6231357FBD5F874FB53F833" box="[1103,1242,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Metazercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the former subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6221356FE91FF37FE00FF76" box="[267,393,152,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6221356FE91FF37FE00FF76" box="[267,393,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">Zerconella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition 
<bibRefCitation id="CB334B15C6221356FD87FF37FD55FF75" author="Blaszak" box="[541,732,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" refString="Blaszak, C. (1975 a) A revision of the family Zerconidae (Acari, Mesostigmata). Systematic studies on family Zerconidae - I. Acarologia, 17, 553 - 569." type="journal article" year="1975" yearSuffix="a">
Błaszak (
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FD10FF37FD4EFF75" box="[650,711,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="1975.0">1975</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned two characters which would distinguish the 
<typeStatus id="70198846C6221356FAF3FF37FA15FF75" box="[1385,1436,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6221356FE89FF12FE15FF11" box="[275,412,189,214]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Metazercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6221356FE89FF12FE15FF11" box="[275,412,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">Metazercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6221356FE7EFF12FD58FF11" box="[484,721,189,214]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leitnerae">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6221356FE7EFF12FD58FF11" box="[484,721,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">Zerconella leitnerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The number of marginal setae is eight in 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6221356FB5BFF12FAC3FF11" box="[1217,1354,189,214]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Metazercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6221356FB5BFF12FAC3FF11" box="[1217,1354,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">Metazercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, seven in 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6221356FF2EFF4DFE28FF3C" box="[180,417,226,251]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leitnerae">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6221356FF2EFF4DFE28FF3C" box="[180,417,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">Zerconella leitnerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the former has a deep incision on posterolateral side of peritrematal shields which is absent in the latter. Later, examining other specimens 
<bibRefCitation id="CB334B15C6221356FCBDFEA7FC7EFEE5" author="Halaskova" box="[807,1015,264,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" refString="Halaskova, V. (1979) Taxonomic studies on Zerconidae (Acari: Mesostigmata) from the Korean People's Democratic Republic. Acta Scientiarum Naturalium Academiae Scientiarum Bohemicae, Brno, 13 (3), 1 - 41." type="journal article" year="1979">
Halašková (
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FC28FEA7FC66FEE5" box="[946,1007,264,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recognised that 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6221356FB2DFEA7FAC9FEE6" box="[1207,1344,264,289]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Metazercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6221356FB2DFEA7FAC9FEE6" box="[1207,1344,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">Metazercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species can have seven or eight pairs of marginal setae on the opisthonotum, and the incision of in the peritrematal shields is often absent. Dorsal gland openings are minute in most of the species, some of them often not visible, but it seems that the second pair of opisthonotal pores (gdJ 
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FC59FED7FC5BFE55" box="[963,978,376,402]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
) is associated with setae J 
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FA88FED7FAA8FE55" box="[1298,1313,376,402]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
(on a line connecting setae J 
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FEEFFE32FE0DFE70" box="[373,388,413,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
and Z 
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FE4CFE32FE6FFE70" box="[470,486,413,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
), while the third pair (gdJ 
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FCBEFE32FCBDFE70" box="[804,820,413,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="4.0">4</number>
) is associated with caudodorsal lobes in the Asian species. It is interesting that some of the species lack one pair of J-setae. Unfortunately no larvae or protonymphs are known from the redefined group, while ontogenetic studies of different 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6221356FB5AFE47FACCFDC5" box="[1216,1349,488,514]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Zerconidae</taxonomicName>
genera show that setae J 
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FEFBFDA2FE04FDE0" box="[353,397,525,551]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
are present in larval stage and J 
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FC8BFDA2FC94FDE0" box="[785,797,525,551]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
appears in protonymphs (
<bibRefCitation id="CB334B15C6221356FBC8FDA2FA06FDE0" author="Lindquist" box="[1106,1423,525,551]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" refString="Lindquist, E. E. &amp; Moraza, M. L. (1998) Observations on homologies of idiosomal setae in Zerconidae (Acari: Mesostigmata), with modified notation for some posterior body setae. Acarologia, 39, 203 - 226." type="journal article" year="1998">
Lindquist &amp; Moraza 
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FAD5FDA2FA06FDE0" box="[1359,1423,525,551]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Presumably the four pairs of larval J-setae are present in each 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6221356FCF3FD9DFC6EFD8C" box="[873,999,562,587]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6221356FCF3FD9DFC6EFD8C" box="[873,999,562,587]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">Zerconella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, while in species having only four pairs of J-setae the protonymphal J 
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FD10FDF7FD1FFDB5" box="[650,662,600,626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
setae are lacking. However the absence of setae J 
<date id="DB1C1024C6221356FA92FDF7FADBFDB5" box="[1288,1362,600,626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FA92FDF7FA9DFDB5" box="[1288,1300,600,626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
may
</date>
be an important derivative character. The zoogeographic distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6221356FC05FDD2FB94FD51" box="[927,1053,637,662]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6221356FC05FDD2FB94FD51" box="[927,1053,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">Zerconella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species suggests that the former character appeared independently in the European and some Asian species, as an evolutionary convergence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF1D36E4C6221356FF5FFD67FBDFFC95" blockId="3.[151,1437,152,850]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">
Besides the above-mentioned characters it is important to note that each species of the redefined genus 
<taxonomicName id="68A24D67C6221356FF0DFD42FE9CFCC1" box="[151,277,749,774]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Zerconella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD6EAF6C6221356FF0DFD42FE9CFCC1" box="[151,277,749,774]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="36">Zerconella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an oblong shape, a relatively small body-size (
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FCEBFD42FC50FCC0" box="[881,985,749,775]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="290.0" valueMax="350.0" valueMin="230.0">230–350</number>
μm) and two or four pairs of strongly sclerotised dorsal cavities. Setae of each species are smooth or very finely pilose, setiform, and often elongate. The genital opening of known males is situated below the line of sternal setae st 
<number id="196A24C3C6221356FBD9FC97FBD8FC95" box="[1091,1105,824,850]" pageId="3" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
.
</paragraph>
